<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,942,1723]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1590,1615]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1959" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1959" box="[606,908,1590,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darlingtoni">
<emphasis box="[606,762,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. darlingtoni</emphasis>
Evans, 1959
</taxonomicName>
by having the clypeal carina high; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the vertex straight; and the mesopleuron with the lower fovea not delimited, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1959" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darlingtoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. darlingtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the clypeal carina low; the antennal scrobe carinate; the vertex convex; and the mesopleuron with the lower fovea delimited.
</paragraph>
